llm_output.rationale: The Use Matrix table shows the Floor Area Ratio (FAR) for the Neighborhood Commercial (N.C.) district in cell (20, 11) as 0.264. This represents the maximum allowed floor area ratio, which is related to the intensity of development and can be used to determine the maximum building size relative to the lot size. While this is not a direct parking requirement, it provides insight into the allowed development intensity which often correlates with parking needs.
